Edgar Ingram and Walter Anderson opened a small restaurant in Wichita,
Kansas. Howard Johnson’s 1925 drug-store soda fountain in Quincy,
Massachusetts, began a chain of roadside restaurants that by 1939 had 132
franchised outlets and in the 1950s and 1960s had a dominant market
